rComments: the absolutely WORST. I got an A+ in this course and even that didn't help me like it any better. Uncaring and makes it impossible to reach her. I learned something but it wasn't inspiring or useful. She shouldn't be teaching and should just stick to law, this is just another source of income for her. 0/10 AVOID
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: I loved this class, the lectures were interesting and all her assignments were fair. The course is not reading heavy at all and the assignments and quizzes really helped prepare me for the final.
She's the best!! So willing to help. Her class isn't easy but definitely manageable if you put in the work
She is an interesting lecturer, but the tests were extremely difficult and assignments were marked harshly and Very little feedback was given.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Taken in Fall of 2015. Breese was the actually the best! She was funny & we used real cases to discuss concepts of law. She was always willing to help & always answered questions. Her powerpoints were fantastic & clear. Quizzes were a great preparation for the exam, as was the Fact Pattern. There are no surprises on her tests.

This class is great! Basic legal principles that are taught using real cases.  There are five pop quizzes, often after each topic is done. The assignments can be challenging but overall an easy class if you get law.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: BEST PROF - She is so good, if you're into law and want to pursue it as a career then this course os perfect - she is inspiring and I want to be her

Her quizzes are OK, not that hard if you read through the slides. She does a review at the beginning of the class for the quiz, which is always good. Her lectures are very interesting, and she always takes the time to answer questions. Assignments, especially fact patterns, are marked harshly though. We're not in law schools yet! :(

Breese Davies is amazing. She is clear, engaging, provides fascinating material and inspires you to do your own critical thinking. Love her, couldn't  recommend her enough.  She frequently gives pop quizzes but always hints at it in advance and they are easy grades if you follow regularly in class (which is not hard since she is very interesting).
Amazing Professor. Keeps you on your toes with pop quizzes and a hard final assignment but truly worth it. I got a lot out of her course. Cannot wait to take another.
BRILLIANT PROFESSOR! Best class I've taken in all of UofT. Such an engaging speaker, class was really interesting, assignments were engaging and very fair. No complaints.

She is very knowledgeable. She knows her material well ('cause she's a lawyer) and presents her lectures in a very organized way. She answers your questions and provides a lot of help on assignments. BUT the assignments were graded too harshly; I felt like we were treated as first year law students. Overall a good learning experience though.

My favourite prof of my first term, which says a lot. Her lectures are engaging, and she presents the material in a clear way without dumbing it down. She also has a great personality and is extremely approachable. The assignments are not easy, but the challenge they provide is welcome. I loved the course and hope to take more of her courses.

I took two classes from her. Criminal law and criminal procedures. She is a great professor and very knowledgable in the topic of law because she is also a lawyer. She is very clear andhelpful when you ask her questions. She is a very direct person. Her assignemnts and exams are not bad. Textbook use is minimal and her markings are seomtiems tough

One of, if not, the best professors I've had the pleasure to being taught by. Took 3 of her courses and although the marking may seem a bit harsh, she is an interesting lecturer who will answer your questions and explain the material as clearly as she can. Great person too.

She's a really great lecturer, which would be expected since she's a lawyer and all that. But like others have mentioned the final exam is HARD. Even though its open book I felt like each question would easily take me a couple of hours at least to finish-hard to do that when you only have 3 hrs to do the whole exam.

Great lecturer, very clear, and very likeable. Like others have mentioned, knows her stuff. BUT-watch out for the final exam! By far the most difficult exam i've EVER had to write ...don't let the 'open book' part fool you! Felt like I was taking the damned LSAT. Overall a great teaching experience-ruined slightly by the ridiculous final exam.

Overall was a good professor with the lectures, clear, concise and very helpful.  BUT watch out for the final Exam.. it was impossible!! It was way to difficult to do properly in just two hours. By far the worst exam I've ever written.
Awesome professor that keeps the class interesting with marks for participation and attendance. Best university experience so far.
Taught the spring semester after Young pulled out. She's a great lecturer but she likes details. There were way too many readings, focus on what she talks about in class and do those readings.

Marks for attendance, her lectures are crystal clear and well organized, tons of reading but it's doable. The 20 page research paper is a bit much but also a good experience. One of my favorite profs at U of T Crim
She talked a bit fast at times but if you've got a laptop, you can keep up.  As a lawyer, she really knew her stuff and is definetly one of my fav. profs
